Condition.RSP.desc: One of my cousin's mother always brag about how her son was able to buy a house immediately after graduating to all her relatives and by extension me. She wouldn't stop going on and on about it during thanksgiving dinner and it irritated the shit out of me. Was it envy? Probably.

Condition.SP.desc: I was talking to my best friend about my grades that I got in college.  Somehow we got on the topic of college life and studying vs. social life.  I bragged about graduating with a 3.96 gpa, but I didn't have a social life. I needed the scholarships to pay for college, and I didn't care about the social life.
a homeless man wanted a quarter to afford a pack of gum. I ended up giving them some dollars.

Condition.RSP.desc: A friend bragged to me about being really good at Overwatch. He was a strong player and proud of his ranking.
